      "comment": "ZIPPING POITIER (4) looks close to another win after finishing third from Box 6 last time (30.79) at Launceston. Must come into calculations. SIMPLY DANGER (2) has some solid form under his belt and proved too classy last time to win by a neck at this track in a handy 20.10 beating Darling Danger. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. Expected to feature again. TWO GIRLS (1) was in the placings last time but shapes well for this on her blistering win the start prior, getting around this track over 340m in 19.18. Has the ability and looks a key chance. WHISKY BARREL (6) is among the chances again if he runs up to the latest effort.",
